### Unit Tests

To run unit tests for this project:

1. Run `mvn clean install`.
2. Open a terminal window in the root directory of the project and run `mvn test`.

### Integration Tests

To run integration tests for this project:

1. Create an environment variable named `CF_API_URL` and set it to the URL of your Cloud Foundry instance. For example:
   ```bash
   export CF_API_URL=https://api.<your-org>.mybluemix.net
   ```

2. Run `mvn clean install`.

You are planning to upgrade your application to use Spark. You want to ensure that your application can continue running after you make changes to your cluster. What should you do? (Choose two)

- A. Use the same version of Spark and YARN.
- B. Use the same version of Spark and Hadoop.
- C. Upgrade your applications to use Spark Streaming.
- D. Upgrade your applications to use Spark SQL.

Spark does not support mixed versions of Hadoop and Spark. Therefore, you need to keep the versions of Hadoop and Spark consistent.
